tanh_header: Tanh {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#9B59B6"
  style.stroke: "#9B59B6"
  style.font-color: white
  style.font-size: 18
  style.bold: true
  width: 300
}
tanh_info: |md
  **Output Range:** (-1, +1)
  **Formula:** tanh(x) = (eˣ - e⁻ˣ)/(eˣ + e⁻ˣ)
  **Derivative:** d/dx tanh(x) = 1 - tanh²(x)
  **Properties:**
  - Zero-centered output
  - Smooth gradients everywhere
  - Can saturate at ±1 (vanishing gradient)
  - Good for hidden layers in small networks
